ce:section.ce:para:
As it explained, gaseous O2 was detected by blowing the gas in to the C-Dots solution as the fluorescence probe and then the calibration curve was drawn (Fig. 12
                           ). Different percentages of O2 were prepared by diluting with N2 gas. For this purpose, the standard gaseous solutions were purged into the C-Dots solution and DO was standardized using the reference O2 sensor. The linear dynamic range was between 3.0 and 48.0%. The limit of detection was found as 0.95% (n=5) with R-squared (R2) of 0.991. The sensitivity of this method was evaluated according to the slope (calibration sensitivity) of the calibration curves (Fig. 12). This value was evaluated to 11.54(a.u.)Lmg−1 for DO with the response time (t

                              90
                           ) of 40.0s. It should be noted that the degree of the reproducibility and repeatability of the gaseous O2 detection were partially similar to those reported for the DO.
